The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Anand, Kramnik split point

Dortmund: GM Viswanathan Anand gave a rock solid performance with black pieces to hold world champion Vladimir Kramnik in the opening round of the Dortmund International Chess Meeting on Saturday. 

GM Shakhriyar Mamedyarov of Azerbaijan, the third seed in the tournament, started off the tournament on a high note by emerging as the lone winner in the first round after defeating local hope GM Arkadij Naiditsch. (PTI) 




